<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 12:58:47 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>Project Zomboid 识别并禁止了十多个 Steam 创意工坊模组，其中包含“严重混淆的代码”，这些代码“创建恶意文件”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/project-zomboid-identifies-and-bans-over-a-dozen-steam-workshop-mods-containing-heavily-obfuscated-code-that-was-creating-malicious-files</link><description>该漏洞仅影响 Project Zomboid 的 Build 42 分支（该游戏当前的“不稳定”测试版本），因此，如果您使用的是 Build 41，则“不​​会受到此特定问题的影响”，开发人员表示。虽然 The Indie Stone 尚未确定恶意文件的实际用途，但“我们强烈建议下载这些文件的任何人采取适当的安全措施，以确保其系统安全。仅仅卸载 mod 是不够的。” &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/project-zomboid-identifies-and-bans-over-a-dozen-steam-workshop-mods-containing-heavily-obfuscated-code-that-was-creating-malicious-files.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 12:58:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/project-zomboid-identifies-and-bans-over-a-dozen-steam-workshop-mods-containing-heavily-obfuscated-code-that-was-creating-malicious-files</guid></item><item><title>斯坦福大学科学家发现隐藏的大脑回路会加剧慢性疼痛</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/stanford-scientists-discover-hidden-brain-circuit-that-fuels-chronic-pain</link><description>科学家们发现了一种以前未知的大脑回路，它似乎会导致慢性疼痛，与负责立即、保护性疼痛反应的通路分开。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/stanford-scientists-discover-hidden-brain-circuit-that-fuels-chronic-pain2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 12:43:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/stanford-scientists-discover-hidden-brain-circuit-that-fuels-chronic-pain</guid></item><item><title>实验室培养的松果体类器官产生褪黑激素，提供新的睡眠模式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/lab-grown-pineal-gland-organoids-produce-melatonin-offering-a-new-sleep-model</link><description>类器官是器官的微型简化版本。在过去的二十年里，科学家们已经为肠道、肺、肝脏、乳腺、大脑等开发了它们。现在，耶鲁大学医学院 (YSM) 的研究人员已经对松果体进行了有机化，松果体是大脑中的一个小结构，通过产生褪黑激素来调节睡眠模式。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/lab-grown-pineal-gland-organoids-produce-melatonin-offering-a-new-sleep-model.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 12:28:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/lab-grown-pineal-gland-organoids-produce-melatonin-offering-a-new-sleep-model</guid></item><item><title>很少使用的胆固醇测试可以预防更多的心脏病和中风</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/little-used-cholesterol-test-could-prevent-more-heart-attacks-and-strokes</link><description>西北医学的一项新研究表明，美国每年有数百万人进行常规血液检查来测量“坏”胆固醇，但这并不是指导治疗和预防心脏病发作和中风的最佳措施&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/little-used-cholesterol-test-could-prevent-more-heart-attacks-and-strokes.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 12:13:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/little-used-cholesterol-test-could-prevent-more-heart-attacks-and-strokes</guid></item><item><title>双管齐下的 NAD 保护：延缓细胞衰老并启动肌肉骨骼再生</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/double%e2%80%90pronged-nad-preservation-delaying-cellular-senescence-and-initiating-musculoskeletal-regeneration</link><description>由 NAD 组成的新型协同药物组合 (N + A) &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/doublee28090pronged-nad-preservation-delaying-cellular-senescence-and-initiating-musculoskeletal-regeneration2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 11:58:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/double%e2%80%90pronged-nad-preservation-delaying-cellular-senescence-and-initiating-musculoskeletal-regeneration</guid></item><item><title>“干细胞检查点”有助于控制干细胞身份</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-stemness-checkpoint-helps-control-stem-cell-identity</link><description>一项研究&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-stemness-checkpoint-helps-control-stem-cell-identity.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 11:43:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-stemness-checkpoint-helps-control-stem-cell-identity</guid></item><item><title>家长和重症监护医师报告的新生儿基因组检测实用性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/parent-and-intensivist-reported-utility-for-neonatal-genomic-testing</link><description>父母和重症医生都认为快速新生儿基因组检测是有益的，特别是对于告知预后而言，尽管一些父母也报告了不确定性或混乱等负面结果。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/parent-and-intensivist-reported-utility-for-neonatal-genomic-testing.png" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 11:28:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/parent-and-intensivist-reported-utility-for-neonatal-genomic-testing</guid></item><item><title>测量分子中电子的磁性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/measuring-an-electrons-magnetism-in-a-molecule</link><description>简单分子离子的精确光谱为量子电动力学的严格测试开辟了一条新途径。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/measuring-an-electrons-magnetism-in-a-molecule.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 11:13:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/measuring-an-electrons-magnetism-in-a-molecule</guid></item><item><title>分子核自旋的光学控制为量子技术指明了新途径</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/optical-control-of-nuclear-spins-in-molecules-points-to-new-paths-for-quantum-technologies</link><description>卡尔斯鲁厄理工学院 (KIT) 的研究人员首次通过光学初始化、控制和读取分子材料中的核自旋态，报告了量子物理和材料科学方面的重要进展。由于核自旋与环境的相互作用较弱，因此是特别稳定的量子信息载体。研究表明， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/optical-control-of-nuclear-spins-in-molecules-points-to-new-paths-for-quantum-technologies.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 10:58:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/optical-control-of-nuclear-spins-in-molecules-points-to-new-paths-for-quantum-technologies</guid></item><item><title>如果暗物质有两种状态怎么办？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/what-if-dark-matter-came-in-two-states</link><description>没有信号本身也可能是一个信号。这是发表在《科学》杂志上的一项新研究背后的想法&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/what-if-dark-matter-came-in-two-states.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 10:43:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/what-if-dark-matter-came-in-two-states</guid></item></channel></rss>